-- HVB Will Introduce Franchised Branches in Germany, FTD Reports
-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 2012-03-21T21:29:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/hvb-will-introduce-franchised-branches-in-germany-ftd-reports.html
HVB Group plans to open franchised
branches in  Germany  to strengthen its retail banking operations,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported in a preview of an article
that will be published tomorrow, citing the German lender.  The offices, equipped by HVB, will be operated by
independent partners who will pay a fee for the branches and
only sell the bank’s products, Peter Buschbeck, head of HVB’s
retail banking operations, said, according to the newspaper.  HVB is Italian bank  UniCredit SpA (UCG) ’s German unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
